doc1056,i was done hoeing out in the fields for the day i was thinking of going i had to leave right away my lif is just fading and oh i felt so alone the nearest young mai was a full day s ri from home my father was reading the holy books in his room my heart was just bleeding i knew i had to go soon he smiled and pointed at an old wooden chair i wanted to hold him but then i just wouldn t dare i said father ther s so much to know ther s a world of things to se and i m ready to go and make a lif for myself if yo giv me what is mine i will go if i can have your blessing but if yo won t bless my journey i m gon na leave anyway son i always tried my best for yo and if yo must be leaving home then go with the blessing of god not too many days later i was well on my way i met a travelling stranger who seemed to have much to say he told me tales of the city and all the women he d had i asked him wasn t that sinful he said no it isn t that bad and then a few days later on an old city road we were drowning in laughter and we had women to hold and this went on quite a long tim my father gave me a lot but when my pockets were empty my friends all left me to rot then a famin hit and drained the land everywhere i looked i saw starvation and a job was nowhere to find i wandered through the city streets competing for the food of common beggers until then i d never known hunger but now i wasn t too proud i finally found some employment feeding pigs on a farm i wasn t treated to kindly i had to sleep in the barn i had to eat with the swine the bread i ate was lik stone it didn t take too much tim until i was dreaming of home oh the servants ther are better fed if i could only have what my father gives them i would truly need nothing more oh i will go and say to him i m no longer worthy to be in your family will yo take me as your servant and let me liv with them it didn t take too long to pack my things i left with only what i wore and i prayed that i still had a home i was near home in si of the house my father just stared dropped open his mouth he ran up the road and fell to my feet and cried and cried father i sinned heaven ashamed i m no longer worthy to wear your name i learned that my home is right where yo are oh father take me in bring the best robe put it on my son shoes for his feet hurry put them on this is my son who i thought had died prepare a feast for my son s aliv i prayed and prayed never heard a sound my son was lost oh thank yo god he s found my son was dead and he s now aliv prepare a feast for my son s aliv my son was dead my son was lost my son s returned in the hands of god,"['i', 'was', 'done', 'hoeing', 'out', 'in', 'the', 'fields', 'for', 'the', 'day', 'i', 'was', 'thinking', 'of', 'going', 'i', 'had', 'to', 'leave', 'right', 'away', 'my', 'lif', 'is', 'just', 'fading', 'and', 'oh', 'i', 'felt', 'so', 'alone', 'the', 'nearest', 'young', 'mai', 'was', 'a', 'full', 'day', 's', 'ri', 'from', 'home', 'my', 'father', 'was', 'reading', 'the', 'holy', 'books', 'in', 'his', 'room', 'my', 'heart', 'was', 'just', 'bleeding', 'i', 'knew', 'i', 'had', 'to', 'go', 'soon', 'he', 'smiled', 'and', 'pointed', 'at', 'an', 'old', 'wooden', 'chair', 'i', 'wanted', 'to', 'hold', 'him', 'but', 'then', 'i', 'just', 'wouldn', 't', 'dare', 'i', 'said', 'father', 'ther', 's', 'so', 'much', 'to', 'know', 'ther', 's', 'a', 'world', 'of', 'things', 'to', 'se', 'and', 'i', 'm', 'ready', 'to', 'go', 'and', 'make', 'a', 'lif', 'for', 'myself', 'if', 'yo', 'giv', 'me', 'what', 'is', 'mine', 'i', 'will', 'go', 'if', 'i', 'can', 'have', 'your', 'blessing', 'but', 'if', 'yo', 'won', 't', 'bless', 'my', 'journey', 'i', 'm', 'gon', 'na', 'leave', 'anyway', 'son', 'i', 'always', 'tried', 'my', 'best', 'for', 'yo', 'and', 'if', 'yo', 'must', 'be', 'leaving', 'home', 'then', 'go', 'with', 'the', 'blessing', 'of', 'god', 'not', 'too', 'many', 'days', 'later', 'i', 'was', 'well', 'on', 'my', 'way', 'i', 'met', 'a', 'travelling', 'stranger', 'who', 'seemed',